skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "ef9804e6-53b3-49e8-9e5a-e13e17d56ab6", "value": "A weapon featuring a single or double edged head attached to a wooden shaft."}

{"id": "a49f0c79-6f26-433a-b89e-803222a21444", "value": "A short stabbing weapon, designed to be fixed to the muzzle of a musket or rifle, even in some cases to pistols. Some were designed to be used both fixed to long guns and independent of them."}
{"id": "444a7eea-818f-42aa-b45d-c103d49523d4", "value": "A rigid holder for a bladed weapon."}

skos:ConceptScheme.dcterms:title: {"id": "ca1ab2f2-6a94-4536-b532-b0d9e1ef2591", "value": "FISH Archaeological Objects Thesaurus"}
skos:ConceptScheme.dcterms:description: {"id": "07493aeb-5ad0-442e-95f4-d52a1261c418", "value": "Originally developed by the Archaeological Objects Working Party and published by the mda. It provides guidance for the recording of archaeological objects in Britain and Ireland covering all historical periods. Now maintained by FISH on behalf of the heritage sector"}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "379d1c76-24c5-4bb7-a119-f6abcfc009e6", "value": "A container in which weapons are put for storage and or transportation."}
{"id": "fa416182-7527-4926-8960-3ed5834fc0ec", "value": "A weapon with a sharp edge or point."}
{"id": "ebdbac9c-34b8-4d0d-bf4a-964206d36ecf", "value": "A short stabbing weapon with a pointed blade. In Medieval period daggers served a dual function being also used as knives."}
{"id": "b2946cfe-6618-49b1-8377-7d552e90fe96", "value": "An axe designed and weighted to be thrown."}
{"id": "84fc80f0-8d34-4810-8ef1-86bb34ab06fb", "value": "A long shafted weapon with a head that can be edged and/or pointed."}

{"id": "4a1a3577-7374-4e7a-b38f-a507dc178fce", "value": "A cutting and thrusting weapon consisting of a blade and a hilt. The blade varies in length and width and the cutting edge can vary from being purely the point to being one or both sides or a combination of these."}
{"id": "3598b1c6-682a-4aa2-ac8e-7a602b331cd9", "value": "A set of shelves."}
{"id": "da2aa3f0-dcd0-4774-a73a-853b3a89f5da", "value": "A flat surface designed to hold objects. For a set of shelves use shelving."}

{"id": "b6c5f723-031f-4f88-a0eb-cee65e3dda20", "value": "A floor composed of small cubes (tesserae) of variously coloured materials (eg tile, stone, marble). In the Roman period, mosaics often depict a religious theme or symbol."}
{"id": "d2adf1b8-ec0a-4189-9f6a-d25ef6ca7b71", "value": "A cube of material used to make up a mosaic."}
{"id": "47009fbf-a395-4ae0-a377-876281181c29", "value": "A projectile fired from a bow."}
{"id": "fdca3a2c-0307-45a5-8351-a3b62640f0eb", "value": "A large, powerful, hand-drawn bow, usually 6 ft (1.8m) in length and traditionally made of wood."}
{"id": "3d122325-a815-4b16-bd64-c0320b7fe9ac", "value": "A weapon for shooting arrows."}
{"id": "75606d40-8f09-4299-94c9-ac68cec552d4", "value": "Algae usually found as a silica skeleton. They obtain their food by photosynthesis and are used in ecological reconstruction."}

{"id": "7a7a474e-57d3-4225-89c7-07294b61f8f0", "value": "Kingdom of living things, lacking chlorophyll, that obtain their food from organic matter, usually by absorption. They include mushrooms, moulds and yeasts."}

{"id": "295380c1-a1cc-4ffb-88b6-c26900f5e954", "value": "Simple organisms, mostly single celled, that move by means of two flagella (complex cellular projections). Most live as marine plankton, but some occur in fresh water. Members of the Kingdom Protista."}
{"id": "799ff1fe-a3b5-4bb9-a4b7-a7c3dd9b3182", "value": "The remains of the fine powdery substance produced by male elements of flowering plants, uniquely identifiable to the species it came from."}
{"id": "4f49ff2c-e4da-47bd-a2c6-4fc86ea69016", "value": "Use for large remains such as fruit, seeds, plant parts, buds etc."}
{"id": "042fe067-ec98-4975-97ad-9b00345a27ab", "value": "Use for the remains of any part of a plant."}
{"id": "8f560022-3ee0-4dec-b12b-28c4d221d900", "value": "Use for microscropic remains."}
{"id": "b46c95c1-5937-4c8a-b3fa-ee2bcb2efd03", "value": "An urn containing a cremation burial."}
{"id": "50b03813-31c7-4904-be69-1c3d1246013c", "value": "The burnt remains of a corpse."}

{"id": "9dcbe7c9-deea-4333-82c6-6d7ae8ad5dde", "value": "Use for the remains of internal parasites of vertebrates, including humans, such as flukes, tapeworm, including their calcified cysts, etc. Eggs of the nematodes Ascaris sp. (maw-worm) and Trichuris sp. (whipworm) are commonly reported."}

{"id": "4dea14d2-ba8d-4d30-b289-e250497b1996", "value": "Remains of parasitic or free-living worms of the phylum Nematoda, characterized as having slender, cylindrical unsegmented bodies. Cysts of Heterodera commonly occur archaeologically"}
{"id": "0f29edea-c9d8-46ce-ae09-ca97747c5679", "value": "Armour designed to protect the torso, and consists of both back and breast plates."}
{"id": "026bfd24-093a-4ddc-ab61-c411bc19651a", "value": "Piece of armour worn to protect the back, often permanently connected to the breastplate."}
{"id": "9287e2ff-8133-4fb3-806d-f1ea929f0ecc", "value": "Characteristic waste flakes struck off in the manufacture of adzes."}
{"id": "5eeb20f0-afb1-441a-bfc5-b16e40d68969", "value": "The piece of stone or flint remaining after flakes have been produced. This is a by-product of tool manufacture."}
{"id": "cc3719b3-91bc-46ed-9530-28e9631d0b73", "value": "A struck piece of flint or other stone where the length is at least twice the width."}
{"id": "b9d5e24b-968f-416c-bba2-8f6a5becf565", "value": "Characteristic waste flakes struck off in the production of axes."}
{"id": "b31eb2c6-fd56-4691-a122-3b9da00d1766", "value": "A flake of stone struck from the core where the length is less than twice the width."}
{"id": "355df4f3-2dc4-4d52-9798-03f4fb72f4f5", "value": "A flake produced from a carefully prepared core."}
{"id": "eb39bd71-daeb-424d-aa30-bb7e6e1f7ac6", "value": "Waste flakes and cores produced in the manufacture of stone implements."}
{"id": "c902d0ad-03e8-48d9-8f73-0073e8aa1a5d", "value": "A collection of objects deliberately grouped together and hidden."}
{"id": "99c7ed29-be56-431d-9c44-afeea9e73b6e", "value": "A necklace or armband made of metal."}
{"id": "c497acc0-01c8-4ad9-8654-f8f13cc1d769", "value": "Pieces of bone used in a game, the pieces are thrown and then picked up between bounces of a small ball or throws of another piece."}

{"id": "1fab989d-aa04-4283-ae5e-e3bd71fdfce7", "value": "An object used for counting, keeping count or marking the position of a player in a game, usually in the form of a small circular-shaped piece of bone, metal, wood, plastic or other material."}
{"id": "e23e4f80-a987-46b1-891b-e2d08ff88393", "value": "A gaming piece used specifically to play chess."}
{"id": "42ad8a54-fee2-4308-a779-437f740de904", "value": "A marker used in the playing of a game."}
{"id": "63c987b4-6f60-46e2-98ba-0c6e6062ddc8", "value": "A playing piece for draughts"}
{"id": "4b36877e-23b7-4004-a9f0-a7913017ff9a", "value": "A gaming piece for the Viking game of Hnefatafl."}
{"id": "b896bb18-50e2-4e3f-a755-2467e82422b8", "value": "A playing piece for the medieval game of table."}
{"id": "58344275-716f-4f96-8951-e3ba1df2341c", "value": "A two dimensional image using paint applied to the surface of a ceiling."}
{"id": "4f206c18-00c6-4877-baa4-f5ec5900acba", "value": "A painting executed directly onto a wall."}
{"id": "32947d88-fc48-4e7f-8c8f-308e24135933", "value": "An object which surrounds or makes up a keyhole."}
{"id": "e165fe91-d983-4cf5-8167-942126df3ac2", "value": "A security device attached to objects."}
{"id": "cddb5243-35d2-4b5c-8050-7455dfeb1c9a", "value": "A device for operating a lock."}
{"id": "dcca0d33-d133-43a5-a773-5f492fbe93ba", "value": "A cutting blade with handle used for food preparation and consumption."}
{"id": "b0b4078f-df6b-4bcf-b529-4ca1109e3cb2", "value": "A leaf or diamond-shaped arrowhead with shallow retouching at the edges."}
{"id": "0869b474-1adc-4c22-ae58-6cef19735913", "value": "A large flake or blade blank thinned on both faces to form an approximate leaf shape. Precise function unknown."}
{"id": "7c828c6a-1bb2-46b7-93a7-6847b46f0e98", "value": "A pestle used specifically for grinding cosmetics."}
{"id": "366fe81c-1c5e-4970-bbe6-a8eb8c71f899", "value": "A mixing or grinding vessel."}
{"id": "0057ed04-eb0e-40b7-9701-460fdf548402", "value": "A mortar used specifically for grinding cosmetics."}
{"id": "db5128a5-f5c2-4001-8874-c1a7911c116b", "value": "A device to hold and rotate food against a heat source during cooking."}
{"id": "a27f161c-3af6-421f-b73e-5456e91f0100", "value": "A device for rotating a spit."}

{"id": "485a26f1-2b83-4850-ab95-e94e402974cf", "value": "Bow Brooch derived from the Colchester type in the mid to late 1st and 2nd centuries AD. Typically the spring is held in a semi-cylindrical crossbar with closed ends and holding the axial bar and a hook or lug on the head to hold the chord."}

{"id": "a7c48657-9040-4edc-b22b-7998c2765742", "value": "A first century AD one-piece bow brooch, one end of which is drawn out to form a spring and pin, characterized by its long, narrow, tapering bow, a small crossbar in front of the spring and a forward hook which holds the spring chord."}
{"id": "663b8c6d-068f-423a-895f-ebbd16052618", "value": "T shaped piece of bronze imitating a key and hung from a chatelaine."}
{"id": "4463c0cb-1f81-4969-9342-8e0904b318b9", "value": "A short chain or chains attached to a woman's belt for carrying keys etc."}
{"id": "1953542b-6485-4f54-a631-c8eef09b04f9", "value": "An image of a deity used as a focus for worship, usually used for non Christian images."}
{"id": "6ac46b1c-c26a-4087-9dc4-633ee1a44adf", "value": "A figure, representation or image, which is itself regarded as sacred."}
{"id": "2298c270-40e5-4643-8453-5a9ebdc21fc2", "value": "A long shafted weapon with a pointed head used for thrusting or as a missile."}
{"id": "c6f8b240-fa17-4d31-8519-7b5c97255060", "value": "The blade or sharp-pointed head attached to the end of a spear's shaft."}

{"id": "92f75733-9e2f-4a65-9fac-7f569271fcd9", "value": "Type of leaf-shaped socketed spearhead with two small holes or loops on either side at the base of the blade. Possibly meant to assist in securing the metal spearhead to the wooden shaft, or to tie streamers of some kind to the top of the spear."}

{"id": "fd54a5ae-e01e-4c12-b56e-ad31d899b61e", "value": "A spearhead with an elongated hollow cast into the base of the blade to receive the end of the wooden spear shaft. The spearhead was secured to the shaft by pegs set at right angles or by lashings fixed to loops cast at the base of the spearhead."}
{"id": "34b41403-551a-474d-899e-e3b992e917a5", "value": "A type of spearhead with a triangular blade bevelled at the edges and with a groove(s) following the outline."}
{"id": "247a6ed9-8987-4625-87f5-c32d2ad919f5", "value": "A sash or belt worn over the shoulder to the hip for carrying a sword."}
{"id": "d41914ec-36d6-42df-ba8f-089d756c5459", "value": "A belt worn around the waist from which a sword is hung. Where worn over the shoulder use baldric."}
{"id": "4f9b54db-ed27-4b7e-b98f-8d454fc240b8", "value": "Objects primarily intended to be used as a medium of exchange, eg coins."}
{"id": "151398b5-fbbf-4bb7-bedf-2bb8e3d43904", "value": "A piece of cast metal obtained from a mould in a form suitable for storage."}
{"id": "d92e9c96-efb2-46f7-b7e0-4ba355000887", "value": "A tool used to filter solid material from liquid by means of a mesh, net or sheet with holes."}
{"id": "d82c7b45-149a-48a8-a9a2-f5a38a6aa45c", "value": "A container with a perforated bottom through which material is shaken or poured."}
{"id": "aed55838-3d9e-4463-87a5-adc642e4c4c2", "value": "A fragment of the base of a vessel, or hollow object, usually of ceramic or glass. If known, use specific vessel type."}
{"id": "48ebd614-5448-4bcc-b8f8-33f4eb6cd484", "value": "A fragment of the body of a vessel, or hollow object, usually of ceramic or glass. If known, use specific vessel type."}
{"id": "2ab71bef-7260-4442-948a-1819fb846703", "value": "A fragment of the rim of a vessel, or hollow object, usually of ceramic or glass. If known, use specific vessel type."}
{"id": "f71d0023-326e-4cc7-ab9f-fd77806b7717", "value": "A fragment of a vessel, or hollow object, usually of ceramic or glass. If known, use specific vessel type."}
{"id": "6587d6db-ffd0-461b-8b45-8af8fc3a3b64", "value": "Use specific form where known."}
{"id": "442fe10a-8360-40db-95d1-f89060051e74", "value": "A piece of fabric with a design, used as an emblem for military or naval purposes, signalling, decoration, display, propaganda etc."}
{"id": "2a45c5b9-4e4e-4bdf-a476-2bfaf1823e12", "value": "A flag bearing a device, often carried on two poles or hanging from a cross piece. Usually used in processions."}
{"id": "25f2eb64-6059-4a54-910d-836c999de082", "value": "A container used to hold ammunition."}
{"id": "d103710b-1b30-484b-920e-3c553ebbf9ea", "value": "A flexible holder for a bladed tool or weapon."}
{"id": "64f16427-6e28-43b3-92f2-6b89571e07e1", "value": "A container for loose gun powder. Sometimes with a regulator to release enough powder for one shot."}

{"id": "0dc15cac-390c-437c-9d42-a533c5ccc8d1", "value": "A flask holding gunpowder used to prime a firearm, ie to provide a small quantity of gunpowder to be put in the pan which would be lit to set off the main charge in the barrel. The powder would often be a finer grade than that used for the charge."}
{"id": "9791ed11-02d9-4ae1-87ad-2d8886bc3f9e", "value": "A horn containing gun powder used for priming a firearm."}
{"id": "2ccd2bd1-84f7-43dd-95e8-f29cf59c513b", "value": "A holder for arrows."}
{"id": "c4e0f9b1-48c9-47ba-89fc-5891ac7be330", "value": "A holder for weapons, explosives and ammunition."}
{"id": "d80caff3-aacf-47b2-b8c8-c8b9dcff7baf", "value": "A horn used to hold loose gun powder for recharging firearms."}
{"id": "66b81a06-654b-4431-99bf-4bcbdcdfaf4a", "value": "Articles used in charging guns and ordnance."}

{"id": "1adcf893-8c39-4be1-beb8-e1fac7aeb1ef", "value": "A vessel composed of three or more separate compartments, joined together and pierced to allow liquid to flow from one to another. There may be one or more handles. (Source: MPRG)"}

{"id": "a0b2031f-6db6-4d82-80c0-7967d82d650e", "value": "A vessel composed of three or more equally spaced lobes and usually, a waisted or pedestal base. The handles are vertical loops, generally of strap form. There may be two opposed handles, or one per lobe junction. (Source: MPRG)"}

{"id": "731410af-7952-4762-b7ab-eb0c86cba419", "value": "A cup with a rounded body beneath a deep neck. There may be a marked junction between neck and body and the angle of the neck may be inward-sloping, upright or everted. (Source: MPRG)"}
{"id": "71a5fdab-e3fe-4bf9-94b8-95fd36abf233", "value": "A cup with convex body walls. (Source: MPRG)"}
{"id": "28f4435f-1d19-42ef-80e1-c61c0ffe765d", "value": "A cup with sides falring outwards from the base towards the rim, usually with a single handle."}
{"id": "308859d5-e071-40c8-a3f8-d49048f05e7b", "value": "A cup with a marked change of angle in the body wall, generally at the point of maximum girth. (Source: MPRG)"}
{"id": "89518fce-63ae-44d6-8ef0-af1437691993", "value": "A cup adapted by the addition of a pedestal base. (Source: MPRG)"}

{"id": "711d8676-84c7-4350-b737-c5017bf6c01e", "value": "A form of cup which incorporates a joke or conundrum, where cut-outs or holes in the body make conventional use impossible. The puzzle is how to drink from it without getting wet; usually achieved by sucking through a hollow rim or handle. (Source: MPRG)"}
{"id": "76a57f2d-a5e3-4a84-91a4-d3e43d4e3811", "value": "A small open container, usually with one handle, used for drinking."}
{"id": "c7d91943-a15f-47cd-aa84-b7d87dce7abe", "value": "A small round dish on which a drinking vessel is set."}
{"id": "595b160a-c6af-401a-8a84-572b9856759b", "value": "A length of cord usually made from twisting fibres together which increases the strength of the rope."}
{"id": "a60e48f9-edef-4187-8a46-c7528e2fe3d5", "value": "Loose fibres obtained by unpicking old ropes. Mainly used to caulk seams in wooden vessels."}
{"id": "50bb0c85-1039-4bfc-9617-edb273103fa3", "value": "A mould used to cast coins."}
{"id": "0f3b9849-46b9-4173-9a0d-3bf78d3c3f12", "value": "A piece of metal, usually cast, struck or stamped, with a definite value."}
{"id": "87d90d26-379c-415e-8e9e-d48d32cad097", "value": "A small shield."}

{"id": "e14ab6a0-2fe4-4ab0-bdcb-cc1cc101259a", "value": "A convex, usually round, piece of metal or other material mounted at the centre of a shield. Originally serving a practical purpose in deflecting blows and providing a mounting for the grip, it later developed into an ornamental feature."}
{"id": "01f3b8ae-eb3a-401b-9d2d-c1783154c8fc", "value": "A protective piece of armour carried in the hand to protect the bearer from weapons."}
{"id": "2c4d2609-1b4a-461c-b179-3f07961e600c", "value": "A type of shield, usually wooden and circular."}
{"id": "6ae11d0f-eab8-4029-be55-c00dcbb1dfd9", "value": "A small round shield."}
{"id": "5c6ca1f8-2f99-4f1e-a85d-0446d98bc510", "value": "An object used to burn incense in."}
{"id": "5ab5d541-43a2-447a-b9ed-79d14b328cd7", "value": "A small spoon used with incense."}
{"id": "92fa8cfe-3db7-44f0-8cef-53c142ee3f49", "value": "Tongs used with incense."}
{"id": "2c71a2ba-2462-43d9-b69d-7f57397b461d", "value": "A container for incense."}
{"id": "57cdc10d-02c3-4fab-93ba-6fba9b37ac27", "value": "A vessel in which incense is burnt."}
{"id": "5e627e12-4deb-4acb-ba19-601d4e65d105", "value": "A container for incense."}
{"id": "11f84185-1dfa-46fe-977c-b1e7a8172781", "value": "A bowl used to contain and burn incense."}
{"id": "972aa1ce-4276-455e-865e-a30b63fff1f7", "value": "A small shovel used with incense."}
{"id": "32d384d7-f988-4e7f-a6b2-b445abb5f2c8", "value": "Woven material."}
{"id": "d0de8a56-dcde-48c8-8861-7028e3f25d12", "value": "A woven fabric used to trim clothes."}
{"id": "9e4d740c-a575-4037-ba5b-67e8182877fc", "value": "A type of fabric often used to trim clothing."}
{"id": "ddf7aa3b-7287-4f65-a581-ad7add14ddc6", "value": "A tool, piece of equipment, container or other object used for or in fishing."}
{"id": "5c16ba28-9309-4782-9b8f-91a79f931409", "value": "A basket for the storage and transport of fishing equipment. For the storage and transport of fish use creel."}
{"id": "ac21792c-44ef-409a-a1ff-e39a0d2410f2", "value": "A wickerwork basket for holding fish or catching lobsters."}
{"id": "cae395c3-7738-4e76-bb6a-edd3ab82e9cf", "value": "A flat object which is broad and rounded at one end and tapers to a handle at the other."}
{"id": "32cd9060-cfd1-4396-909e-138314f40f0f", "value": "A tool used to examine or explore a cavity eg surgically for exploring the depth and direction of wounds."}
{"id": "f2b46c65-a795-4087-aaa5-8b37f80fb813", "value": "A pointed two-edged surgical knife."}
{"id": "32e7a5b3-1a03-45c0-acb4-a7cfa8391744", "value": "A small knife used in surgery."}
{"id": "6e91e151-6ac8-48eb-b872-6f773b459869", "value": "An instrument used for surgery, which is the treatment of injuries by instruments and manually."}
{"id": "04e226b7-364c-48a6-a3ad-661b8749a566", "value": "An instrument in the form of a pair of pincers used to grip and pull objects, usually used in surgery."}
{"id": "570da677-2beb-46da-9d9c-b384a5db77cd", "value": "A thin, pointed implement used for sewing with a hole at the blunt end for threading the sewing material."}
{"id": "9985f855-9ea3-4a98-8ffd-b3c6efdca306", "value": "An instrument for holding back a part of a body eg an organ."}
{"id": "3322cbce-1a5a-4cbf-963f-6af4f12c1e41", "value": "A portable beehive, often made of straw."}
{"id": "ee69f315-12e8-4355-a362-c88de0e560af", "value": "A receptacle used as a home for bees, traditionally made of thick straw work in the shape of a dome,but sometimes made of wood."}
{"id": "88baaaf4-e9e8-4d98-8c18-305e947097db", "value": "Wax used to seal letters, envelopes, documents, etc."}
{"id": "fad2ee6d-33be-453c-8beb-12005e97fd2f", "value": "The tool used to create a mark on pottery by the potter."}
{"id": "094978c0-61bb-4002-b5ac-ff9269fb3f34", "value": "Semi precious stone or glass engraved with a design and used to make an impression on wax or clay."}
{"id": "660b1af8-fedb-4cc1-881e-97d43e278388", "value": "A stamp, made of clay or stone, used to mark bars of eye ointment."}
{"id": "75cee163-aab8-4d78-b2bd-b3ede3e5f02f", "value": "An ancient Egyptian gem cut in the shape of a scarab beetle and engraved with symbols on its flat side."}
{"id": "eb3e4388-70f7-4d48-8428-128e997a447c", "value": "The object used to make impressions in wax as seals."}
{"id": "fce7443c-f39a-44e3-8f8f-1441fb6df233", "value": "A container in which the Sacrament is carried."}
{"id": "0153d921-0e22-4e3a-9e11-52f88bf83c6f", "value": "A container for a pyx which is often a canopied niche in a wall."}
